<h2>Solar Incentives in Orlando</h2>
<p>Orlando residents have access to several valuable solar incentives that significantly reduce installation costs. The federal solar Investment Tax Credit (ITC) provides a 30% tax credit on the total system cost through 2032, then decreases to 26% in 2033 and 22% in 2034. Florida offers additional benefits including no state income tax on solar investments and a property tax exemption for the added home value from solar installations. Duke Energy participates in net metering, allowing customers to receive retail rate credits for excess solar energy fed back into the grid. The state also exempts solar equipment from sales tax, providing immediate savings of 6% to 7.5% depending on local tax rates. Additionally, Florida's renewable energy property tax exemption means the added home value from solar panels won't increase property taxes, making solar an even more attractive long-term investment for Orlando homeowners.</p>

<h2>Best Solar Companies in Orlando</h2>
<p>When selecting a solar installer in Orlando, prioritize companies with proper Florida licensing, including an electrical contractor license and solar contractor certification. Look for installers with extensive local experience who understand Orlando's specific permitting requirements and Duke Energy's interconnection procedures. Top-rated companies typically offer comprehensive warranties covering equipment (20-25 years), workmanship (10-25 years), and performance guarantees. Verify the installer's Better Business Bureau rating, read recent customer reviews, and request references from local installations. Quality installers will conduct thorough site assessments, provide detailed proposals with multiple financing options, and handle all permit applications and utility interconnection paperwork. Avoid door-to-door sales companies and instead focus on established local businesses with permanent Orlando locations. The best installers will also provide ongoing monitoring services and maintenance support throughout your system's lifetime, ensuring optimal performance in Orlando's climate conditions.</p>

